The paper focuses on botnet detection, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and Lanczos method, which are both commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical optimization (cs.NE). The paper also deals with processing large amounts of data in real-time, which is a topic related to systems and networking (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves matrix operations and optimization, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
